<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="475" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,258,317]" pageId="14" pageNumber="475">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,258,283]" pageId="14" pageNumber="475">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A completely black almost totally lustrous species with elongate first flagellomere and very long setae on head and thorax; 1+3 dorsocentral setae; legs black but apical one third of tibiae and all tarsomeres yellow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/890361/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="475" targetBox="[207,1378,413,1854]" targetPageId="14">
